.TH "lpfc_bg_err_opcodes" 9 "lpfc_bg_err_opcodes" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_bg_err_opcodes \- reDetermine the BlockGuard opcodes to be used with the specified SCSI command in order to force a guard tag error.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lpfc_bg_err_opcodes
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ","
.BI "struct scsi_cmnd *sc "  ","
.BI "uint8_t *txop "  ","
.BI "uint8_t *rxop "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
The Hba for which this call is being executed.
.IP "sc" 12
The SCSI command to examine
.IP "txop" 12
(out) BlockGuard operation for transmitted data
.IP "rxop" 12
(out) BlockGuard operation for received data
.SH "RETURN"
zero on success; non-zero if tx and/or rx op cannot be determined
